text: Sycamore Strip Airport is a public airport located eight miles (12.9 km) southwest of the central business district (CBD) of Fort Worth, in Tarrant County, Texas, United States. The airport is used solely for general aviation purposes including aircraft rental and flight school. More information available at the airport's website. == Facilities == Sycamore Strip Airport has one runway: * Runway 17/35: 3,970 x 30 ft. (1,210 x 9 m), Surface: Concrete == External links == Category:Airports in Fort Worth, Texas Category:Airports in Tarrant County, Texas
